-- China Renews Subsidy to Rooftop Solar Projects, China Daily Says
-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 2013-01-04T19:55:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-04/china-renews-subsidy-to-rooftop-solar-projects-china-daily-says.html
China has approved a plan to provide
subsidies to rooftop solar installations,  China Daily  reported,
citing the Ministry of Housing and Urban-Rural Development.  Subsidies will range from 7.5 yuan ($1.2) to 9 yuan per
watt, totaling 1.82 billion yuan for a batch of 126 approved
projects, the newspaper said.  The nation has since 2009 started programs to boost the use
of solar energy from rooftop installations, China Daily said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
